Sarvam is more than just a band.

Sarvam is an amalgamation of different minds coming together to form what is one of Chennai's most exciting Progressive Carnatic fusion acts.
In the current musical sphere that is dominated by the monotony of mainstream songwriting, Sarvam emerges as a force that is both boundary-pushing yet grounded. The extreme diverse influences of various band members, that range from progressive rock/metal to new-age electronica, are effortlessly woven together to bring about a sound that is both fresh and exciting but still is neatly held together with a string of familiarity, that is Indian Classical music.

Quick Bio:
I'm a musician/producer just enjoying what I do! I began playing (more like toying around) with an electric keyboard (A Casio I think it was . . . probably anyways) when I was 9 years old; this is truly what got me started loving synthesized sound; plus add in the 80's synth pop music that seemed to fill my house whilst growing up.

My main goal today is in elevating my skills to match that of the top producers of today. I want to learn as much as I can (and then some) and raise the level of quality material I put out all whilst developing my own "so called" sound.

Overall, I love being able to create . . . and this is my preferred avenue to do so . . .

Never stop learning and loving.
